1  9  4  7  年   9  月

3
00:01:29,803 --> 00:01:32,356
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}是数学家赢得了世界大战
Mathematicians won the war.

4
00:01:33,234 --> 00:01:36,491
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}是数学家破解了日本密码
Mathematicians broke the Japanese codes...

5
00:01:36,564 --> 00:01:38,685
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}发明了原子弹
...and built the A-bomb.

6
00:01:38,763 --> 00:01:41,986
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}同你们一样的数学家
Mathematicians... like you.

7
00:01:42,825 --> 00:01:46,752
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}苏联的终极目标是赤化全世界
The stated goal of the Soviets is global communism.

8
00:01:46,823 --> 00:01:48,700
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}在医学、经济
In medicine or economics,

9
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:51,000
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}科技、太空领域
in technology or space,

10
00:01:51,387 --> 00:01:53,246
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}战线已经建立
battle lines are being drawn.

11
00:01:54,151 --> 00:01:56,942
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}为了争取胜利，我们需要结果
To triumph, we need results.

12
00:01:57,015 --> 00:01:59,976
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}可以发表和应用的结果
Publishable, applicable results.

13
00:02:00,046 --> 00:02:04,542
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}那么你们当中谁将是下一个摩尔斯?
Now who among you will be the next Morse?

14
00:02:04,542 --> 00:02:05,834
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}下一个爱因斯坦?
The next Einstein?

15
00:02:06,675 --> 00:02:08,700
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你们当中谁将是
Who among you will be the vanguard

16
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:12,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}民主、自由和探索的先锋?
of democracy, freedom, and discovery?

17
00:02:12,802 --> 00:02:15,100
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}今天，我们将美国的未来
Today, we bequeath America's future

18
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:17,700
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}交到你们的手中
into your able hands.

19
00:02:18,632 --> 00:02:20,787
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}欢迎加入普林斯顿，先生们
Welcome to Princeton, gentlemen.

20
00:02:38,317 --> 00:02:40,541
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}汉森拿到卡内基奖学金居然还不满足
It's not enough Hansen won the Carnegie Scholarship.

21
00:02:40,616 --> 00:02:42,635
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他想要自己独享
No, he has to have it all for himself.

22
00:02:43,713 --> 00:02:44,900
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这是第一次由两人共享
It's the first time the Carnegie prize...

23
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,876
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}卡耐基奖学金，汉森都要气死了
...has been split. Hansen's all bent.

24
00:02:46,876 --> 00:02:49,237
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}听说他一心想进入惠勒研究室
Rumor is he's got his sights set on Wheeler Lab,

25
00:02:49,308 --> 00:02:51,274
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}就是麻省理工学院的新军事智囊团
the new military think tank at M.I.T.

26
00:02:51,474 --> 00:02:54,002
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}今年他们只收一个人
They're only taking one this year.

27
00:02:54,072 --> 00:02:55,863
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}而汉森当第一人选当习惯了
Hansen's used to being picked first.

28
00:02:55,937 --> 00:02:57,627
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}是啊，他搞数学真是屈才了
Oh, yeah, he's wasted on math.

29
00:02:57,703 --> 00:02:59,892
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他应该去选总统
He should be running for president.

30
00:03:09,993 --> 00:03:11,700
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你的领带这么烂
There could be a mathematical explanation

31
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:13,500
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}一定有数学上的合理解释
for how bad your tie is.

32
00:03:19,352 --> 00:03:20,406
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}谢谢你
Thank you.

33
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:24,006
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我是尼尔森，专攻符号密码学
Neilson, symbol cryptography.

34
00:03:24,006 --> 00:03:25,300
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他破解过日本密码
Neils here broke a Jap code.

35
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}帮助了世界摆脱法西斯主义
Helped rid the world of fascism.

36
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:30,000
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}起码他对女生都是这么说的，是吧?
At least that's what he tells the girls, Neils?

37
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我叫本德尔，专攻原子物理学
The name's Bender. Atomic physics.

38
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,962
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-你是哪位?  -我迟到了吗?
-And you are?  -Am I late?

39
00:03:33,962 --> 00:03:35,530
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-是啊  -是啊，苏先生
-Yes.  -Yes, Mr. Sol.

40
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:38,761
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}噢，好吧，你好
Oh, good. Hi.

41
00:03:38,764 --> 00:03:39,891
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我是理查德・苏
Sol. Richard Sol.

42
00:03:39,891 --> 00:03:41,423
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这就是天才的负担
The burden of genius.

43
00:03:41,423 --> 00:03:43,691
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-他来了  -应酬这么多，时间却这么少
-There he is.  -So many supplicants, and so little time.

44
00:03:43,691 --> 00:03:45,554
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-苏先生  -你好啊，伙计
-Mr. Sol.  -How are you, sir?

45
00:03:45,631 --> 00:03:47,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-本德尔  -很高兴见到你
-Bender.  -Nice to see you.

46
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,496
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}恭喜你，汉森先生
Congratulations, Mr. Hansen.

47
00:03:48,496 --> 00:03:49,185
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}谢谢
Thank you.

48
00:03:49,862 --> 00:03:51,687
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}再给我一杯
I'll take another.

49
00:03:52,693 --> 00:03:53,713
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}什么?
Excuse me?

50
00:03:53,792 --> 00:03:56,681
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}万分抱歉，我以为你是服务生
A thousand pardons. I simply assumed you were the waiter.

51
00:03:56,681 --> 00:03:57,379
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}给他留点面子，汉森
Play nice, Hansen.

52
00:03:57,379 --> 00:03:59,109
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}给人留面子可不是汉森的派头
Nice is not Hansen's strong suit.

53
00:03:59,109 --> 00:04:00,247
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}真是无心之过
Honest mistake.

54
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:03,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}唔，马丁・汉森
Well, Martin Hansen.

55
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,000
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}是马丁，没错吧?
It is Martin, isn't it?

56
00:04:05,683 --> 00:04:07,111
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}没错，约翰，我就是
Why, yes, John, it is.

57
00:04:07,615 --> 00:04:10,667
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我猜你对误估已习以为常了吧
I imagine you're getting quite used to miscalculation.

58
00:04:13,478 --> 00:04:16,962
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我读过你的初稿
I've read your pre-prints.

59
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:18,264
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}两份都读过
Both of them.

60
00:04:18,339 --> 00:04:20,100
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}有关纳粹密码文件的那份
The one on Nazi ciphers,

61
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:23,100
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}和有关非线性方程式的另外那份
and the other one on non-linear equations,

62
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,027
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}而我无比确信...
and I am supremely confident...

63
00:04:25,027 --> 00:04:26,293
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}不管是哪一份都不具备...
that there is not a single seminal...

64
00:04:26,368 --> 00:04:28,421
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}任何有价值或者新颖的观点
...or innovative idea in either one of them.

65
00:04:32,129 --> 00:04:33,785
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}好好享受你的水果酒
Enjoy your punch.

66
00:04:38,225 --> 00:04:39,912
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}各位，来会会约翰・纳什
Gentlemen, meet John Nash,

67
00:04:40,556 --> 00:04:42,688
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}神秘的西弗吉尼亚州天才
the mysterious West Virginia genius.

68
00:04:42,688 --> 00:04:45,774
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}著名的卡内基奖学金的另外那位得主
The other winner of the distinguished Carnegie Scholarship.

69
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,900
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}当然了
Of course.

70
00:05:20,991 --> 00:05:23,010
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}真要命
Oh, Christ.

71
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:26,279
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}浪子室友到了
The prodigal roommate arrives.

72
00:05:27,387 --> 00:05:28,107
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}室友?
Roommate?

73
00:05:28,819 --> 00:05:30,475
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}天啊，饶了我吧
Oh, God, no.

74
00:05:32,149 --> 00:05:35,871
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你知道所谓的宿醉...
Did you know that having a hangover is...

75
00:05:35,947 --> 00:05:38,374
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}就是体内没有足够的水份
...is not having enough water in your body

76
00:05:38,445 --> 00:05:40,635
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}去执行克雷布斯循环吗?
to run your Krebs cycles?

77
00:05:40,810 --> 00:05:43,462
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这和你渴死时的发生的状况
Which is exactly what happens to you

78
00:05:43,462 --> 00:05:45,006
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}是完全一样的
when you're dying of thirst.

79
00:05:45,006 --> 00:05:48,694
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}所以说，渴死的感觉...
So, dying of thirst...

80
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:53,387
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}可能就像是宿醉...
would probably feel pretty much like the hangover...

81
00:05:53,387 --> 00:05:56,221
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}最后特么醉死了一样
that finally bloody kills you.

82
00:05:58,363 --> 00:05:59,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}约翰・纳什?
John Nash?

83
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,100
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你好
Hello.

84
00:06:01,593 --> 00:06:02,887
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我叫查尔斯・赫曼
Charles Herman.

85
00:06:03,359 --> 00:06:05,114
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}很高兴认识你
Pleased to meet you.

86
00:06:21,878 --> 00:06:23,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}唔，正式宣布
Well, it's official.

87
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,300
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我几乎又是个人了
I'm almost human again.

88
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,899
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}警官，我看到撞我的司机了
Officer, I saw the driver who hit me.

89
00:06:26,974 --> 00:06:29,199
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他的名字是"约翰尼沃克"（著名威士忌品牌）
His name was Johnny Walker.

90
00:06:35,301 --> 00:06:36,600
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}呃，昨天晚上我...
Well, I got in last night

91
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,700
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}准时赶上了...
in time for...

92
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,900
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}英文系办的鸡尾酒会
English department cocktails.

93
00:06:40,497 --> 00:06:42,182
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}鸡是我的
Cock was mine,

94
00:06:42,182 --> 00:06:44,053
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}尾是那个特别年轻可人的小玩意儿
the tail belonged to a particularly lovely young thing

95
00:06:44,053 --> 00:06:45,991
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}她还崇拜...
with a passion for...

96
00:06:46,891 --> 00:06:49,978
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}D.H.劳伦斯（著名的情欲作家） 你不怎么容易被打扰，是吧?
D.H. Lawrence. You're not easily distracted, are you?

97
00:06:50,206 --> 00:06:51,182
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我是来工作的
I'm here to work.

98
00:06:51,256 --> 00:06:52,877
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}唔，是吗? 那当然
Hmmm, are you? Right.

99
00:06:52,877 --> 00:06:54,800
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我明白了，哇哦!
I see. Crikey!

100
00:07:04,611 --> 00:07:06,670
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我的室友是个傻逼吗?
Is my roommate a dick?

101
00:07:10,608 --> 00:07:14,365
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我说，既然我们之间的冰山打不破
Listen. If we can't break the ice...

102
00:07:14,837 --> 00:07:16,731
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}把它给淹了怎么样?
How about we drown it?

103
00:07:27,528 --> 00:07:29,084
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}那么你有什么故事?
So what's your story?

104
00:07:30,193 --> 00:07:33,552
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}一个从没出过家门的穷小孩?
You the poor kid that never got to go to Exeter or Andover?

105
00:07:34,388 --> 00:07:36,006
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}虽然从小接受高等教育
Despite my privileged upbringing,

106
00:07:36,006 --> 00:07:37,687
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}不过我也算是平衡发展
I'm actually quite well-balanced.

107
00:07:37,687 --> 00:07:39,172
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我和别人互相嫌弃的程度都差不多
I have a chip on both shoulders.

108
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,600
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你大概就是比较擅长
Maybe you're just better

109
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,800
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}应付数字而不是人
with the old integers than you are with people.

110
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:46,660
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我的小学老师，她跟我说
My first grade teacher, she told me

111
00:07:46,660 --> 00:07:48,500
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我有两个大脑
that I was born with two helpings of brain,

112
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,940
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}却只有半颗心
but only half a helping of heart.

113
00:07:50,009 --> 00:07:51,494
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-真的?  -嗯
-Really?  -Yeah.

114
00:07:51,576 --> 00:07:54,300
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}哇! 她听上去很可爱!
Wow! She sounds lovely!

115
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:56,800
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}其实我...
The truth is that I...

116
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我不喜欢人们
I don't like people much.

117
00:07:59,836 --> 00:08:01,621
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他们也不喜欢我
And they don't much like me.

118
00:08:01,622 --> 00:08:02,800
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}怎么可能?
But why,

119
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,900
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你这么聪慧又迷人
with all your obvious wit and charm?

120
00:08:07,497 --> 00:08:08,353
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}说真的，约翰
Seriously, John.

