{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-没问题  -谢谢你们!
-Not a problem.  -Thank you so much!

498
00:31:44,374 --> 00:31:46,461
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-休息一下!  -好嘞!
-At a break!  -Got it!

499
00:31:51,202 --> 00:31:53,530
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你们会发现在多变性的微积分中
As you will find in multivariable calculus,

500
00:31:53,530 --> 00:31:55,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}往往会有...
there is often...

501
00:31:55,698 --> 00:31:58,390
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}一题多解的情况
a number of solutions for any given problem.

502
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:04,616
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}如我所言，这道题
As I was saying, this problem here

503
00:32:05,424 --> 00:32:08,250
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}有些人会解上好几个月
will take some of you many months to solve.

504
00:32:08,822 --> 00:32:11,011
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}而其他人
For others among you,

505
00:32:11,987 --> 00:32:14,642
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}则会花上一辈子的时间
it will take you the term of your natural lives.

506
00:32:29,206 --> 00:32:30,997
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}纳什教授
Professor Nash.

507
00:32:44,127 --> 00:32:45,600
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我是威廉・帕彻
William Parcher.

508
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:49,200
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}老大哥
Big brother,

509
00:32:49,457 --> 00:32:50,942
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}为您效劳
at your service.

510
00:32:51,389 --> 00:32:54,512
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我能为国防部做些什么?
What can I do for the Department of Defense?

511
00:32:54,967 --> 00:32:56,361
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你是来替我加薪的吗?
Are you going to to give me a raise?

512
00:32:56,433 --> 00:32:58,361
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}咱们散散步
Let's take a walk.

513
00:32:59,530 --> 00:33:02,787
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}-你在五角大楼的工作让人钦佩  -的确如此
-Impressive work at the Pentagon.  -Yes, it was.

514
00:33:02,861 --> 00:33:04,080
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}奥本海默 (原子弹之父) 说过
Oppenheimer used to say,

515
00:33:04,080 --> 00:33:06,580
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}"天才会先于问题而看见答案"
"Genius sees the answer before the question."

516
00:33:06,580 --> 00:33:08,720
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你认识奥本海默?
You knew Oppenheimer?

517
00:33:08,790 --> 00:33:11,245
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他的计划就是在我的监督之下进行的
His project was under my supervision.

518
00:33:11,245 --> 00:33:13,177
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}哪个计划?
Which project?

519
00:33:16,083 --> 00:33:16,909
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}那个计划
That project.

520
00:33:16,983 --> 00:33:18,673
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}其实并没有那么简单，你明白吗?
It's not that simple, you know?

521
00:33:19,081 --> 00:33:20,373
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你们可结束了战争啊
Well, you ended the war.

522
00:33:20,447 --> 00:33:24,067
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我们烧死了十五万人
We incinerated 150,000 people in a heartbeat.

523
00:33:24,144 --> 00:33:27,004
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}伟大的事迹都伴随着巨大的代价，帕彻先生
Great deeds come at great cost, Mr. Parcher.

524
00:33:28,275 --> 00:33:30,567
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}评判是非功过的权力
Well, conviction, it turns out,

525
00:33:30,639 --> 00:33:34,067
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}可是旁观者才拥有的奢侈品，纳什先生
is a luxury of those on the sidelines, Mr. Nash.

526
00:33:35,736 --> 00:33:37,994
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我会试着记住的
I'll try and keep that in mind.

527
00:33:40,765 --> 00:33:43,980
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}那么约翰，你没家人
So John, no family,

528
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:46,027
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}也没有密友...
no close friends...

529
00:33:46,027 --> 00:33:47,284
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}何以至此?
Why is that?

530
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:49,878
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我喜欢归结于自己是个独狼的缘故
I like to think it's because I'm a lone wolf.

531
00:33:50,924 --> 00:33:53,477
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}不过主要是因为人们不喜欢我
But mainly it's because people don't like me.

532
00:33:55,254 --> 00:33:56,780
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}唔，在某些需要苦心孤诣的时候
Well, there are certain endeavors

533
00:33:56,780 --> 00:33:58,186
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}缺乏人际交往
where your lack of personal connection

534
00:33:58,186 --> 00:34:00,345
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}反倒会被视为一项优势
would be considered an advantage.

535
00:34:02,847 --> 00:34:04,303
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这里是管制区
This is a secure area.

536
00:34:04,306 --> 00:34:05,871
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他们认识我
They know me.

537
00:34:08,977 --> 00:34:10,130
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你来过这里吗?
Have you ever been here?

538
00:34:10,209 --> 00:34:12,080
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}在刚来的时候他们介绍说
We were told during our initial briefing

539
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,707
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这些仓库都被废弃了
that these warehouses were abandoned.

540
00:34:13,707 --> 00:34:16,725
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}不完全正确
That's not precisely accurate.

541
00:34:54,076 --> 00:34:55,702
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}等我告诉了你下面的内容
By telling you what I'm about to tell you,

542
00:34:55,702 --> 00:34:57,580
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}就相当于把你的保密权限提升到了
I am increasing your security clearance

543
00:34:57,580 --> 00:34:59,080
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}最高机密
to top secret.

544
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:02,822
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}泄露机密资料会招致牢狱之灾
Disclosure of secure information can result in imprisonment.

545
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:04,057
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}懂吗?
Get it?

546
00:35:05,300 --> 00:35:06,520
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}什么行动?
What operation?

547
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,700
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}由战略行动办公室制作

548
00:35:12,028 --> 00:35:13,684
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这东西挺好用的
Those are a good idea.

549
00:35:17,723 --> 00:35:19,880
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这家工厂位于柏林
This factory is in Berlin.

550
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:21,580
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我们在战争行将结束时占领了它
We seized it at the end of the war.

551
00:35:21,588 --> 00:35:23,280
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}纳粹工程师正试图
Nazi engineers were attempting

552
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,718
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}造出轻型原子弹
to build a portable atomic bomb.

553
00:35:25,718 --> 00:35:28,470
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}苏联在我们前面抵达了这个设施
The Soviets reached this facility before we did,

554
00:35:28,470 --> 00:35:30,513
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我们丢失了该死的资料
and we lost the damn thing.

555
00:35:32,513 --> 00:35:35,441
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}五角大楼的路线顺序
The routing orders at the Pentagon,

556
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:38,167
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}它们跟这个有关，不是吗?
they were about this, weren't they?

557
00:35:38,408 --> 00:35:41,100
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}苏联内部并没有人们所认为的那样统一
The Soviets aren't as unified as people believe.

558
00:35:41,100 --> 00:35:44,680
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}一小股自称 "新自由" 的红军
A faction of the Red Army calling itself Novaya Svobga,

559
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:46,898
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}控制了原子弹
"the New Freedom" has control of the bomb

560
00:35:46,898 --> 00:35:49,327
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}并且打算在美国本土引爆
and intends to detonate it on U.S. soil.

561
00:35:50,398 --> 00:35:54,382
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他们打算造成最大的平民伤亡
Their plan is to incur maximum civilian casualties.

562
00:35:58,092 --> 00:36:00,480
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}人类是能做到可以想见的
Man is capable of as much atrocity

563
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:02,680
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}最极端的残忍的
as he has imagination.

564
00:36:04,087 --> 00:36:07,242
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}新自由在美国有间谍
New Freedom has sleeper agents here in the U.S.

565
00:36:08,617 --> 00:36:10,680
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}麦卡锡议员是个白痴
McCarthy is an idiot,

566
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:12,680
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}不幸的是这并不意味着他是错的
but unfortunately that doesn't make him wrong.

567
00:36:14,014 --> 00:36:16,737
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}新自由是通过报纸和杂志上的密码
New Freedom communicates to its agents

568
00:36:16,812 --> 00:36:19,171
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}同其间谍进行通讯的
through codes imbedded in newspapers and magazines,

569
00:36:19,242 --> 00:36:21,280
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这正是我们需要你的地方
and that's where you come in.

570
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:22,780
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你瞧，约翰
You see, John,

571
00:36:23,007 --> 00:36:25,333
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你鹤立鸡群的地方
what distinguishes you

572
00:36:25,405 --> 00:36:27,061
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}在于你是...
is that you are,

573
00:36:27,137 --> 00:36:28,793
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}简单来说
quite simply,

574
00:36:28,869 --> 00:36:32,489
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}一名我所见过最好的、天生的密码破译者
the best natural code-breaker I have ever seen.

575
00:36:38,695 --> 00:36:41,350
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你到底要我干什么?
What exactly is it that you would like me to do?

576
00:36:46,789 --> 00:36:49,281
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}把这份期刊列表记下来
Commit this list of periodicals to memory.

577
00:36:51,251 --> 00:36:52,938
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}仔细浏览每期新刊
Scan each new issue,

578
00:36:53,417 --> 00:36:54,780
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}只要发现密码
find any hidden codes,

579
00:36:54,780 --> 00:36:56,480
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}就破解掉它
decipher them.

580
00:36:58,580 --> 00:37:00,680
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}把下巴放在下巴台上
Place your chin on the chin rest.

581
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:01,778
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}凝视灯光
Stare into the light.

582
00:37:01,778 --> 00:37:04,231
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}脉搏88，正常
Pulse 88, regular.

583
00:37:06,973 --> 00:37:09,558
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这个会有点不舒服
Okay, this may be a little uncomfortable.

584
00:37:12,003 --> 00:37:14,194
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}有点痛，对不对?
That's got a little zap to it, doesn't it?

585
00:37:15,133 --> 00:37:17,890
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}他只是植入了一个镭二极管
He just implanted a radium diode.

586
00:37:17,965 --> 00:37:19,518
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}别担心，很安全
Don't worry, it's safe.

587
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:22,655
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}它会周期性衰变
The isotope decays predictably.

588
00:37:22,728 --> 00:37:25,885
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}使得这些数字定期更换
As a result, these numbers change over time.

589
00:37:26,159 --> 00:37:28,677
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}那是你进入投信点的密码
They're the access codes to your drop spot.

590
00:37:30,955 --> 00:37:33,939
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}那我现在成什么了，一个密探?
So what am I now, a spy?

591
00:37:47,343 --> 00:37:48,500
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}进来
Come.

592
00:37:52,638 --> 00:37:54,834
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}天呐，你一定很重要
Boy, you must be really important.

593
00:38:02,997 --> 00:38:04,653
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}没事了，麦克
It's all right, Mike.

594
00:38:14,755 --> 00:38:15,709
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你在做什么?
What are you working on?

595
00:38:18,552 --> 00:38:19,775
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}这是机密
Classified.

596
00:38:21,149 --> 00:38:23,134
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}我们已经等了半个钟头
Everyone waited half an hour.

597
00:38:23,214 --> 00:38:24,870
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}等什么?
For?

598
00:38:25,346 --> 00:38:26,203
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你的课呀
Class.

599
00:38:26,945 --> 00:38:29,338
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}你今天没来上课
You missed class today.

600
00:38:29,410 --> 00:38:31,668
{\3c&H000000&\bord1.5\fn微软雅黑}噢，我估摸着...
Oh. I suspect that...

